## 1. PROJECT SUMMARY

**Name:** Mafia Wars  
**Type:** Browser-based party game (Mafia / Werewolf-style social deduction)  
**Tagline:** "Fast party nights. Secret roles. Perfect shuffle."  
**Stack:** React 19 + TypeScript + Vite 7 (single-page app, no backend)  
**Architecture:** Everything lives in one main component (`src/App.tsx` ~1350 lines). No routing library. No database. State is React `useState` only.  
**Deployment model:** Static frontend. Online "rooms" are share-link placeholders — there is no real multiplayer server yet.

### What the app does
1. Shows a cinematic landing screen (auto-advances after 5 seconds)
2. Lets players choose **Offline** (tabletop host) or **Online** (share a room link)
3. Lobby: add players by name + emoji avatar, toggle optional roles, configure game settings
4. Shuffles and assigns secret roles as flip cards
5. Runs structured **Night** and **Day** phases with voting, abilities, and event logs
6. Detects win conditions and shows a post-game summary
7. Saves last 20 game results to `localStorage`

